Ten-hut!

02:18.400 --> 02:20.260
Welcome home, Mr. President.

02:20.440 --> 02:22.900
Over here, Mr. President!

02:23.070 --> 02:24.150
Good to be home.

02:26.700 --> 02:28.440
Thank you.

02:39.540 --> 02:41.950
- What do you got?
- Let's go over it again.

02:42.750 --> 02:44.620
Who do I see first this morning?

02:44.800 --> 02:46.410
You've got Mr. Crenshaw at 11:30.

02:46.590 --> 02:49.710
I can't do two things at once, you know?
I got NSC at 2:30.

02:49.880 --> 02:52.000
- That'll only take half an hour.
- With Syria?

02:52.180 --> 02:54.140
You've got that radio address
to go over...

02:54.310 --> 02:58.100
...and the Legal Counsel speech
at the Monroe tomorrow night.

02:58.520 --> 03:01.010
- The Monroe?
- Welcome home, Mr. President.

03:01.190 --> 03:03.020
Yes, sir, the Monroe Hotel.

03:03.190 --> 03:05.180
Have you got someone to double
for me there?

03:05.360 --> 03:07.320
- We're working on it, sir.
- Good.

03:09.490 --> 03:11.850
Try to find someone
who looks like me this time.

03:12.030 --> 03:14.240
That last guy was a joke.

03:17.410 --> 03:20.000
Ladies and gentlemen, here he is...

03:20.170 --> 03:22.410
...the President of the United States.

03:35.560 --> 03:37.720
God bless you. Thank you.

03:37.890 --> 03:40.630
Welcome to Durenberger's, Mr. President.

03:40.810 --> 03:42.520
Thank you, one and all.

03:42.690 --> 03:46.230
Let me just say,
from one chief executive to another...

03:46.400 --> 03:51.860
...that there is no Chevrolet
like Durenberger's Community Chevrolet.

03:52.030 --> 03:53.770
Thank you, Mr. President.

03:53.950 --> 03:57.070
- Mom, that's not the president, is it?
- I sure hope not.

03:57.240 --> 04:02.360
I have the feeling that when people
find out about the $500 cash rebate...

04:02.540 --> 04:05.580
...on all Geo Storms
and Geo Storm convertibles...

04:05.750 --> 04:07.990
...that you're going to be even busier
than I am.

04:08.170 --> 04:10.160
You said it, Mr. President.

04:11.050 --> 04:14.960
See, I could veto this Simpson-Gardner
thing if I wanted to, but I don't want to.

04:15.140 --> 04:17.170
Do you know why I don't want to?

04:18.140 --> 04:20.130
It's got homeless shelters...

04:20.310 --> 04:22.350
...Head Start centers...

04:22.520 --> 04:23.560
...and, uh....

04:23.730 --> 04:25.190
Hot lunches.

04:25.360 --> 04:26.940
Hot lunches for little kiddies.

04:28.690 --> 04:32.190
If I kill it, I'm gonna look like a prick.

04:32.360 --> 04:34.600
I don't want to look like a prick.

04:35.030 --> 04:36.490
I want you to look like pricks.

04:38.160 --> 04:40.620
But, sir, we've tried to kill it.

04:40.790 --> 04:41.820
Twice.

04:42.000 --> 04:45.790
I don't think so, Howard, no.
If you'd killed it, it would be dead.

04:45.960 --> 04:47.830
When I kill something...

04:48.000 --> 04:49.790
...it always dies.

04:49.960 --> 04:51.830
- Doesn't it, Bob?
- Always did.

04:53.260 --> 04:56.340
Mr. President, with the work your wife
has done with the homeless--

04:56.510 --> 04:58.110
My wife.

04:58.510 --> 04:59.550
Norman.

04:59.720 --> 05:02.930
I don't want you to do this
because you're forced to.

05:03.100 --> 05:05.720
I want you to do this
because you want to.

05:06.440 --> 05:09.480
I want you to do it
because it's the right thing to do.

05:09.650 --> 05:14.110
I want you to do it because you're acting
in the best interests of your country.

05:17.870 --> 05:19.320
Well, I think that's it.

05:32.920 --> 05:34.080
- 6:30?
- Oh-ho!

05:34.260 --> 05:37.050
- Perfect.
- Great. I'll see you then.

05:37.550 --> 05:39.010
- How are you? Having fun?
- Hey.

05:39.180 --> 05:42.170
Yes. Good to see you.

05:42.350 --> 05:43.560
Ask me how I did.

05:43.730 --> 05:46.060
- How did it go? Yeah?
- I killed them. It was great.

05:46.230 --> 05:48.390
- See what you can do in here.
- Okay, what's up?

05:48.560 --> 05:50.850
Hey. How are you, Mabel? Hi, Jennifer.

05:51.020 --> 05:54.520
Mabel says it's too far on the bus.
Jennifer's boss tried to hit on her.

05:54.690 --> 05:57.810
And Lola's been in your office crying
for almost an hour.

05:57.990 --> 05:59.070
Lola, what happened?

05:59.240 --> 06:02.230
Oh, Mr. Kovic, it's not my fault.
I learn on the IBM, okay?

06:02.410 --> 06:04.030
- Yeah.
- Then they put me on the Wang.

06:07.210 --> 06:09.870
Don't worry. We'll think of something.

06:10.040 --> 06:12.660
Yeah. So tonight's the big night.

06:12.840 --> 06:15.250
Yeah. It's some big secret.
He won't tell me.

06:15.420 --> 06:16.880
Can't get out of it.

06:17.880 --> 06:19.670
It's gonna be fine.
We're gonna fix it.

06:19.840 --> 06:23.090
Honey, call, uh, Murray.
Tell him we're on our way, okay?

06:23.260 --> 06:25.300
It's Wednesday.
Everybody works on Wednesday.

06:25.480 --> 06:27.970
Can I borrow your--? Thanks.

06:29.350 --> 06:31.440
Don't cry. Murray.

06:31.610 --> 06:33.890
Dave, I can't hire anybody else. I can't.

06:34.070 --> 06:36.350
Murray, she flies on an IBM.

06:36.530 --> 06:40.360
I don't have enough work
for the people you already gave me.

06:40.530 --> 06:43.200
She's got three kids.
Her husband's a diabetic. Diabetic?

06:46.960 --> 06:49.320
Just a short-term thing.
Straight temp job.

06:50.790 --> 06:54.540
Please? Murray. Murray.

06:54.710 --> 06:56.370
I'll see what I can do.

06:59.840 --> 07:01.180
Thanks.

07:03.010 --> 07:04.630
You feel okay about this?

07:04.810 --> 07:06.300
Not yet.

07:06.470 --> 07:08.140
You will.

07:08.310 --> 07:10.270
Do you want to go play some ball?

07:10.900 --> 07:13.480
It's the middle of the afternoon.
I'm working.

07:13.650 --> 07:16.140
Me too. Okay, well, um, thanks, Murray.

07:16.320 --> 07:17.350
I'll see you tomorrow.

07:17.530 --> 07:20.900
- Bye, Lola, Kate, Adriana, Pam.
- Bye, Dave.

